In this "disorder" is born an electromagnetic wave (of light, infrared, ultraviolets, etc.), and this wave is nothing but a photon; that is, one of the bosons "power carriers".
More stable field
The same happens with the Higgs boson, with the difference that it is another field, the Higgs field, which needs to be "disordered" for this boson to appear.
Now, the Higgs field is much more stable than the electromagnetic field. To activate it, it takes to reach extremely high energies, a little like it was an iced pond in which only a thick rock could slip through the surface.
